My own little thingy: "I am  the ancient god. I war in sorrow I die in peace, my soul lifes to fight."</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/ujefm.showPublicProfile?language=EN>jefm</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(12/16/01 5:32:41 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Battle Damage</span><hr size=1> Whoohoo...<br>
I knew those years of being a lame quake skinner would pay off<br>
Burns...like scorch marks from something...<br>
if it's a head on shot and not deflected just put a dot and then draw lines radiating from it...it'll turn out...(you might want to do a big one over the rocket launcer area to show carbonizing) if you do in in photoshop use blending modes...everything will turn out great<br>
if it's a glancing blow...it'll have a direction...just do the origin then draw lines in that direction...it's a little trickier because size and speed of what hit it will affect the pattern...like something faster and smaller will have a narrow streak and probably longer...a large slow object will be almost like a direct shot except it will be lopsided more to one side...<br>
dent's are easy...just vary the shading...<br>
bullet holes are the same...just make a circle and fill it with a sunburst gradient (I think that's what it is)...then do lighting effects and go opposite the normal way...then toss a dot in the middle...there is better ways but that's the quick and dirty method...rember though exit wounds are different from entry...<br>
entry holes are usually clean...exit wounds (if the projectile exits)...are usually bad and have massively torn material...you poked your pencil through paper before...thats what the exit hole looks like...except metal...<br>
torn metal is also cool...and rust<br>
Look at skinning tutorials....they have the best stuff for that...if you need more detailed or better methods or something I didn't talk about...just ask <p><pre>
